    "created_at": "2015-11-06T12:33:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-11-06T12:33:32Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hmm so some thoughts about this - the current level design is using `AttackMove` on an actor with `AutoTarget>AllowMovement:false` defined, meaning that `AutoTarget`should not alter the movement.\n\nWouldn't it be more sane to have a move command that did that instead of using this hacky behaviour? So move-and-attack-anything-you-come-across-without-stopping\n\nCurrently this is only explicitely done, so if you give an attack order to a turreted unit and order it to move, it will keep attacking. Wouldn't it be useful for units to do that automatically according to their stance? (iirc turreted units in the original ts did that)\n"
  },
