    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This patch on top of yours will make the gunboat work again (it basically undoes the changes from your second commit if `OnRails` is set). This is ugly, but at least it keeps all the `OnRails` hackery in the same place (`AttackFollows`).\n\n``` diff\ndiff --git a/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Attack/AttackFollow.cs b/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Attack/AttackFollow.cs\nindex 6280de3..3582f5e 100644\n--- a/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Attack/AttackFollow.cs\n+++ b/OpenRA.Mods.Common/Traits/Attack/AttackFollow.cs\n@@ -56,6 +56,7 @@ class AttackActivity : Activity\n                {\n                        readonly AttackFollow attack;\n                        readonly IMove move;\n+                       readonly bool onRailsHack;\n                        readonly Target target;\n                        readonly bool forceAttack;\n\n@@ -64,10 +65,13 @@ public AttackActivity(Actor self, Target target, bool allowMove, bool forceAttac\n                                attack = self.Trait<AttackFollow>();\n                                move = allowMove ? self.TraitOrDefault<IMove>() : null;\n\n-                               // HACK: Mobile.OnRails is horrible\n+                               // HACK: Mobile.OnRails is horrible. Blergh.\n                                var mobile = move as Mobile;\n                                if (mobile != null && mobile.Info.OnRails)\n+                               {\n                                        move = null;\n+                                       onRailsHack = true;\n+                               }\n\n                                this.target = target;\n                                this.forceAttack = forceAttack;\n@@ -96,11 +100,15 @@ public override Activity Tick(Actor self)\n\n                                        if (move != null)\n                                                return Util.SequenceActivities(move.MoveFollow(self, target, weapon.Weapon.MinRange, maxRange), this);\n-                                       if (target.IsInRange(self.CenterPosition, weapon.MaxRange()) && !target.IsInRange(self.CenterPosition, weapon.Weapon.MinRange))\n+                                       if (!onRailsHack &&\n+                                               target.IsInRange(self.CenterPosition, weapon.MaxRange()) &&\n+                                               !target.IsInRange(self.CenterPosition, weapon.Weapon.MinRange))\n                                                return this;\n                                }\n\n-                               attack.Target = Target.Invalid;\n+                               if (!onRailsHack)\n+                                       attack.Target = Target.Invalid;\n+\n                                return NextActivity;\n                        }\n                }\n```\n\nAn alternative would be a new `AttackTurretedOnRails` trait + activity combo that would inherit from `AttackTurreted` to just overwrite  the `GetAttackActivity` method to return the new activity, which would basically be a duplicate of `AttackFollow`'s `AttackActivity`, only with all the mobile/move stuff removed.\n"
